Resistors in parallel have the&nbsp;<b>same pd</b>, the current passing through a parallel combination of resistors is equal to the&nbsp;<b>sum of the individual currents</b>.<br><ul><li>\(I_1=\frac{V}{R_1}\)<br></li><li>\(I_2=\frac{V}{R_2}\)<br></li><li>\(I=I_1+I_2=\frac{V}{R_1}+\frac{V}{R_2}\)</li><li>Since&nbsp;\(I=\frac{V}{R}\),&nbsp;\(\frac{1}{R}=\frac{1}{R_1}+\frac{1}{R_2}\)</li></ul>